<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1543&amp;p=13237#p13237"><![CDATA[
Well I find that method of joy reading to be inefficient and fugly (the CMP could be avoided altogether, and the AND is rather strange).  To disect code like this, all you have to do is break it down step by step.  Every instruction does a very small task, and if you look at what each instruction is doing, you can figure out what the whole block of code is doing.<br /><br />This code in paticular makes heavy use of the C flag.  So knowing how the C flag works with ROL and CMP is vital to understanding this code.  Knowing what the $4016 register does is also important.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Mon May 22, 2006 8:54 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
